s it.\n\nThe scene shifts to a plain white background where two small red tablet-like circles move across the screen. Black text appears: “Opens Nasal Passages” and “Relieves Sinus Pressure.” At the bottom, smaller grey text reads, “Use only as directed.” The Sudafed box then appears large on a light blue background, again labeled “Non-Drowsy SUDAFED,” “Maximum Strength,” and “Nasal Decongestant,” with “Use only as directed” underneath.\n\nBack in the home, the man now stands smiling in front of a beige door with a round yellow doorknob. He looks clear-headed and cheerful. The woman stands behind him, smiling too, and wraps the navy scarf with red stripes around his neck. He stands upright with his hands near his waist, looking pleased and alert, while she adjusts the scarf over his shoulders and around his collar. The motion is lively and slightly overlapping, with the scarf flipping and swinging as she finishes arranging it.\n\nThe man turns his head toward the woman and smiles. She moves close behind him, then reaches around and places her hands on his cheeks, gently checking his face and nose. He puckers his lips briefly as she presses his cheeks, then smiles again. They end standing close together by the door, both cheerful; her hand rests on his shoulder and his hands settle confidently at his sides. The final image returns to the Sudafed package on the light blue background, prominently displaying “Non-Drowsy SUDAFED Maximum Strength Nasal Decongestant.”",
